name: Angela Merkel
biography: Angela Dorothea Merkel is a German politician who served as the Chancellor of Germany from 2005 to 2021. She is a member of the Christian Democratic Union and is known for her leadership in the European Union and handling of various global issues.

name: Joe Biden
biography: Joseph Robinette Biden Jr. is an American politician who has been serving as the 46th President of the United States since 2021. He previously served as the Vice President of the United States under President Barack Obama.

name: Xi Jinping
biography: Xi Jinping is a Chinese politician who has been the General Secretary of the Communist Party of China since 2013. He has also served as the President of China and the Chairman of the Central Military Commission.

name: Vladimir Putin
biography: Vladimir Vladimirovich Putin is a Russian politician and former intelligence officer who has been serving as the President of Russia since 1999, except for a period as Prime Minister from 2008 to 2012. He is known for his strongman image and assertive foreign policy.

name: Emmanuel Macron
biography: Emmanuel Jean-Michel Frédéric Macron is a French politician who has been serving as the President of France since 2017. He is the founder of the political party La République En Marche! and is known for his centrist policies.

name: Narendra Modi
biography: Narendra Damodardas Modi is an Indian politician who has been serving as the Prime Minister of India since 2014. He is a member of the Bharatiya Janata Party and is known for his economic and social reforms.

name: Boris Johnson
biography: Alexander Boris de Pfeffel Johnson is a British politician who has been serving as the Prime Minister of the United Kingdom since 2019. He is a member of the Conservative Party and is known for his distinctive style and approach to politics.

name: Shinzo Abe
biography: Shinzo Abe is a Japanese politician who served as the Prime Minister of Japan from 2012 to 2020. He is a member of the Liberal Democratic Party and is known for his economic policies and foreign relations.

name: Jacinda Ardern
biography: Jacinda Kate Laurell Ardern is a New Zealand politician who has been serving as the Prime Minister of New Zealand since 2017. She is a member of the Labour Party and is known for her empathetic leadership and progressive policies.

name: Jair Bolsonaro
biography: Jair Messias Bolsonaro is a Brazilian politician and retired military officer who has been serving as the President of Brazil since 2019. He is a member of the Social Liberal Party and is known for his conservative and nationalist views.

name: Justin Trudeau
biography: Justin Pierre James Trudeau is a Canadian politician who has been serving as the Prime Minister of Canada since 2015. He is a member of the Liberal Party and is known for his progressive policies and emphasis on diversity.

name: Andrés Manuel López Obrador
biography: Andrés Manuel López Obrador, often referred to as AMLO, is a Mexican politician who has been serving as the President of Mexico since 2018. He is a member of the National Regeneration Movement and is known for his populist policies.

name: Erna Solberg
biography: Erna Solberg is a Norwegian politician who served as the Prime Minister of Norway from 2013 to 2021. She is a member of the Conservative Party and is known for her focus on education and economic policies.

name: Scott Morrison
biography: Scott John Morrison is an Australian politician who has been serving as the Prime Minister of Australia since 2018. He is a member of the Liberal Party and is known for his conservative policies and background in marketing.

name: António Costa
biography: António Luís Santos da Costa is a Portuguese politician who has been serving as the Prime Minister of Portugal since 2015. He is a member of the Socialist Party and is known for his efforts to stabilize the economy and promote social welfare.

name: Recep Tayyip Erdoğan
biography: Recep Tayyip Erdoğan is a Turkish politician who has been serving as the President of Turkey since 2014. He is a member of the Justice and Development Party and has played a significant role in Turkish politics for many years.

name: Andrzej Duda
biography: Andrzej Sebastian Duda is a Polish lawyer and politician who has been serving as the President of Poland since 2015. He is a member of the Law and Justice party and is known for his conservative views.

name: Moon Jae-in
biography: Moon Jae-in is a South Korean politician who has been serving as the President of South Korea since 2017. He is a member of the Democratic Party and is known for his efforts to improve inter-Korean relations.

name: Cyril Ramaphosa
biography: Matamela Cyril Ramaphosa is a South African politician who has been serving as the President of South Africa since 2018. He is a member of the African National Congress and played a crucial role in the transition to democracy in South Africa.

name: Volodymyr Zelensky
biography: Volodymyr Oleksandrovych Zelensky is a Ukrainian politician and comedian who has been serving as the President of Ukraine since 2019. He is known for his unconventional background and his showbiz career before entering politics.

name: Alberto Fernández
biography: Alberto Ángel Fernández is an Argentine politician and lawyer who has been serving as the President of Argentina since 2019. He is a member of the Justicialist Party and is known for his efforts to address economic challenges.

name: Michelle Bachelet
position: United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights
biography: Verónica Michelle Bachelet Jeria is a Chilean politician who has served as the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights since 2018. She previously served as the President of Chile from 2006 to 2010 and from 2014 to 2018.

name: Pedro Sánchez
biography: Pedro Sánchez Pérez-Castejón is a Spanish economist and politician who has been serving as the Prime Minister of Spain since 2018. He is a member of the Spanish Socialist Workers' Party and is known for his handling of various domestic and international issues.

name: Benjamin Netanyahu
biography: Benjamin Netanyahu is an Israeli politician who served as the Prime Minister of Israel for multiple terms. He is a member of the Likud party and is known for his conservative views and leadership during times of conflict.

name: Imran Khan
biography: Imran Ahmad Khan Niazi is a Pakistani former cricketer and politician who has been serving as the Prime Minister of Pakistan since 2018. He is the founder of the political party Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf and is known for his efforts to address corruption and improve governance.

name: Tsai Ing-wen
biography: Tsai Ing-wen is a Taiwanese politician and lawyer who has been serving as the President of Taiwan since 2016. She is a member of the Democratic Progressive Party and is known for her stance on Taiwan's sovereignty.

name: Jacques Chirac
biography: Jacques René Chirac was a French politician who served as the President of France from 1995 to 2007. He was a member of the Rally for the Republic party and is remembered for his domestic and foreign policies.

name: Hassan Rouhani
biography: Hassan Rouhani is an Iranian politician and cleric who served as the President of Iran from 2013 to 2021. He is a member of the Moderation and Development Party and is known for his efforts to improve relations with the international community.

name: Raul Castro
biography: Raúl Modesto Castro Ruz is a Cuban politician and revolutionary who served as the First Secretary of the Communist Party of Cuba from 2011 to 2021. He played a key role in the Cuban Revolution and the leadership of the country.

name: Mahathir Mohamad
biography: Tun Dr. Mahathir bin Mohamad is a Malaysian physician and politician who served as the Prime Minister of Malaysia in two non-consecutive terms, from 1981 to 2003 and from 2018 to 2020. He is known for his modernization efforts and economic policies.

name: Lenin Moreno
biography: Lenín Moreno Garcés is an Ecuadorian politician who served as the President of Ecuador from 2017 to 2021. He is a member of the Alianza PAIS party and is known for his focus on social welfare programs and disability rights.

name: David Cameron
biography: David William Donald Cameron is a British politician who served as the Prime Minister of the United Kingdom from 2010 to 2016. He is a member of the Conservative Party and is known for his leadership during the Brexit referendum.

name: Lee Hsien Loong
biography: Lee Hsien Loong is a Singaporean politician who has been serving as the Prime Minister of Singapore since 2004. He is a member of the People's Action Party and is known for his economic and technological initiatives.

name: Abdel Fattah el-Sisi
biography: Abdel Fattah Saeed Hussein Khalil el-Sisi is an Egyptian politician and military officer who has been serving as the President of Egypt since 2014. He previously served as the Commander-in-Chief of the Egyptian Armed Forces.

name: Juan Orlando Hernández
biography: Juan Orlando Hernández Alvarado is a Honduran politician and lawyer who has been serving as the President of Honduras since 2014. He is a member of the National Party and has focused on security and economic issues.

name: Abiy Ahmed
biography: Abiy Ahmed Ali is an Ethiopian politician who has been serving as the Prime Minister of Ethiopia since 2018. He is a member of the Prosperity Party and is known for his efforts to promote political and economic reforms.

name: Nicolás Maduro
biography: Nicolás Maduro Moros is a Venezuelan politician who has been serving as the President of Venezuela since 2013. He is a member of the United Socialist Party and has faced significant domestic and international challenges during his tenure.

name: Hun Sen
biography: Hun Sen is a Cambodian politician who has been serving as the Prime Minister of Cambodia since 1985. He is a member of the Cambodian People's Party and has played a central role in Cambodian politics for decades.

name: Khaleda Zia
biography: Begum Khaleda Zia is a Bangladeshi politician who served as the Prime Minister of Bangladesh in two non-consecutive terms, from 1991 to 1996 and from 2001 to 2006. She is a member of the Bangladesh Nationalist Party.

name: Lee Kuan Yew
biography: Lee Kuan Yew was a Singaporean politician who served as the Prime Minister of Singapore from 1959 to 1990. He is considered the founding father of modern Singapore and played a crucial role in its transformation into a developed nation.

name: Aung San Suu Kyi
biography: Aung San Suu Kyi is a Burmese politician and Nobel Peace Prize laureate who served as the State Counsellor of Myanmar from 2016 to 2021. She is a member of the National League for Democracy and is known for her nonviolent struggle for democracy and human rights.

name: Lee Hoi-chang
biography: Lee Hoi-chang is a South Korean politician and lawyer who served as the Prime Minister of South Korea from 1993 to 1998. He is a member of the Liberty Korea Party and has been an influential figure in South Korean politics.

name: Lee Myung-bak
biography: Lee Myung-bak is a South Korean businessman and politician who served as the President of South Korea from 2008 to 2013. He is a member of the Grand National Party and is known for his economic policies and infrastructure projects.

name: Sheikh Hasina
biography: Sheikh Hasina is a Bangladeshi politician who has been serving as the Prime Minister of Bangladesh since 2009. She is a member of the Awami League and has played a significant role in shaping the country's politics and development.

name: Stefan Löfven
biography: Stefan Löfven is a Swedish politician who served as the Prime Minister of Sweden from 2014 to 2021. He is a member of the Social Democratic Party and has been a prominent figure in Swedish politics for several decades.

name: Klaus Iohannis
biography: Klaus Werner Iohannis is a Romanian politician who has been serving as the President of Romania since 2014. He is a member of the National Liberal Party and is known for his background in physics and his tenure as mayor of Sibiu.

name: Evo Morales
biography: Evo Morales is a Bolivian politician and former coca farmer who served as the President of Bolivia from 2006 to 2019. He is a member of the Movement for Socialism party and is known for his indigenous rights and social welfare policies.

name: Joko Widodo
biography: Joko Widodo, also known as Jokowi, is an Indonesian politician who has been serving as the President of Indonesia since 2014. He is a member of the Indonesian Democratic Party and is known for his infrastructure and social welfare initiatives.

name: Enrique Peña Nieto
biography: Enrique Peña Nieto is a Mexican politician who served as the President of Mexico from 2012 to 2018. He is a member of the Institutional Revolutionary Party and is known for his economic and energy reforms.

name: François Hollande
biography: François Gérard Georges Nicolas Hollande is a French politician who served as the President of France from 2012 to 2017. He is a member of the Socialist Party and is known for his economic policies and foreign relations.
